-假设菲比是我的伴娘… -太棒了

11
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,690
Hypothetically.
那只是假设

12
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:36,990
Still.
一样啦

13
00:00:38,430 --> 00:00:42,430
If Phoebe were mine, Rachel would be Phoebe's, I'd be Rachel's.
如果菲比是我的伴娘，瑞秋是菲比的伴娘，我是瑞秋的伴娘

14
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:45,200
We all get to do it and no one gets upset.
我们都可以当伴娘 没有人会难过

15
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:49,740
-That's a pretty good idea. -I'll do that. So, who's yours?
-那是个好主意 -我要参加，谁会是你的伴娘？

16
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:54,640
Well,that's the best part. You guys get to decide.
那是最棒的 你们得决定谁是我的伴娘

17
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,820
-Why is that the best part? -I don't have to.
-为什么那是最棒的？ -这样我就不必决定了

18
00:01:01,290 --> 00:01:06,250
Of course we'll help you decide. We'll do anything we can to help you.
当然我们会帮你决定 我们会尽力帮你

19
00:01:06,490 --> 00:01:07,980
I'd like to make a toast.
我想要举杯

20
00:01:08,830 --> 00:01:11,300
To the future Mrs. Chandler Bing...
敬未来的钱德宾太太…

21
00:01:12,130 --> 00:01:16,230
my best friend and truly one of the nicest people that..
我最好的朋友跟最棒的…

22
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:18,330
-Really not deciding. -Fine.
-我真的还没有决定 -好吧

23
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:22,870
Excuse me, I couldn't help overhearing.
对不起，我不是故意要偷听的

24
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:25,510
-You're marrying Chandler Bing? -Yeah.
-你要嫁给钱德宾？ -对

25
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:28,140
Good luck!
祝你好运！

26
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,280
Oh,and good luck to you too!
我也祝你好运

27
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:34,650
What a nice lady.
她真是好心

28
00:01:36,290 --> 00:01:38,380
The One With Nap Partners
本集播出：午睡的同伴

00:01:39,290 --> 00:01:40,380
rainystar压制iPod-MP4

29
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,730
Yeah!
太棒了

30
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:21,330
-Die Hard,still great. -Yep.
-《终极警探》还是很好看 -没错

31
00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:23,770
Let's make it a double feature?
要看第二只片子吗？

32
00:02:23,970 --> 00:02:25,230
What else you rent?
你还租了什么？

33
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:27,800
Die Hard 2.
《终极警探续集》

34
00:02:28,810 --> 00:02:30,740
Joey, this is Die Hard 1 again.
乔伊，这也是《终极警探1》

35
00:02:32,150 --> 00:02:36,210
Well, we'll watch it a second time and it's Die Hard 2.
我们要再看一遍 那就等于是《终极警探续集》

36
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:40,010
-Joey,we just saw it. -And?
-乔伊，我们刚刚才看完第一集 -所以呢？

37
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:42,280
It would be cool to see it again!
再看一次一定很酷

38
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:45,320
-Yeah! Die Hard! -Die Hard!
-太棒了，《终极警探》 -《终极警探》

39
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,990
Dude, you didn't say Die Hard.
兄弟，你没有说《终极警探》

40
00:02:49,930 --> 00:02:51,490
Is everything okay?
你还好吗？

41
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,430
Yeah, I just got plans.
还好，只是我有别的事要做

42
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:57,970
Well, John McClane had plans.
约翰麦克连也有别的事要做

43
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:01,930
I want to leave before Joey gets all worked up...
我想在乔伊大开杀戒…

44
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:04,510
and starts calling everybody "bitch."
开始叫大家“混蛋”前离开

45
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:08,640
What are you talking about, bitch?
你在胡说什么？混蛋

46
00:03:11,690 --> 00:03:13,240
-Hey, Rachel. -Yeah?
-嘿，瑞秋 -什么事？

47
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:16,980
When I get married, will you be my maid of honor?
我结婚时，你愿意当我的伴娘吗？

48
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:18,630
Really?
真的吗？

49
00:03:19,130 --> 00:03:22,150
Oh, my God, Phoebe. I mean I'm just..
我的天啊，菲比 我是说我…

50
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,830
Wait a minute.
等一下

51
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,760
If I'm your maid of honor, that means that you are Monica's.
如果我是你的伴娘 那表示你是摩妮卡的伴娘

52
00:03:30,970 --> 00:03:32,370
Oh.
喔

53
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,900
Well,if that's what you want.
如果你真的想那么做随便你

54
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,770
No way,Phoebe. I want to be Monica's.
想都别想，菲比 我想当摩妮卡的伴娘

55
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:43,280
-Why does it even matter? -Why does it matter to you?
-为什么这件事这么重要？ -你为什么觉得它很重要？

56
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:45,680
Because this one is now.
因为她马上就要结婚了

57
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,760
And it's two of our best friends.
我们两个最好的朋友要结婚了

58
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:51,460
And who knows what you're gonna marry.
谁知道你会嫁给什么样的人

59
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:56,690
What if I marry Ross? or Joey?
如果我嫁给罗斯呢？或乔伊？

60
00:03:58,070 --> 00:03:59,530
You wouldn't.
你不会的

61
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:05,500
Okay, look, Rachel. I know you really want to do this...
好吧，听我说，瑞秋 我知道你真的想当摩妮卡的伴娘…

62
00:04:05,710 --> 00:04:09,040
but I've never been maid of honor to anyone before.
但我从来没有当过伴娘

63
00:04:09,310 --> 00:04:11,400
I know you've done it at least twice.
我知道你至少当过两次伴娘

64
00:04:11,650 --> 00:04:14,480
-Yeah, but Phoebe..  -Please let me finish.
-对，但是菲比… -请你让我把话说完

65
00:04:16,180 --> 00:04:17,810
I guess that was it.
我猜我已经说完了

66
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:20,920
Okay.
好吧

67
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:25,380
Since you've never done it before, you can be Monica's maid of honor.
既然你没有当过伴娘 你可以当摩妮卡的伴娘

68
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:27,650
Oh,thank you so much!
谢谢你

69
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,590
Yay.
好耶

70
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:35,390
I'm gonna marry someone good.
我一定会嫁给好男人

71
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,360
Oh, I know.
我知道

72
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:39,130
Better than Chandler.
比钱德还棒

73
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:02,090
-What happened? -I don't know.
-发生了什么事？ -我不知道

74
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:05,160
We fell asleep. That is all.
我们睡着了，就那么简单

75
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:07,860
Yeah. Yeah? Yeah.
对，对吗？对

76
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,540
All right, well, I'd better go.
好了，我得走了

77
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:13,710
-I think that would be best. -Yeah.
-我想那是最好的 -没错

78
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:15,600
-I'll talk to you later. -Okay.
-我待会再跟你谈 -好

79
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:19,210
-But not about this. -No,never. Never!
-但千万别谈这件事 -没错，永远都别提

80
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,980
-Bye. -No touch. No touch.
-再见 -别碰我

81
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,150
Hey,a weird thing happened at brunch.
我去吃早午餐时发生了一件怪事

82
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,880
This woman overheard that I was marrying you...
有个女人不经意听到 我要嫁给你…

83
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:35,990
and she wished me good luck.
她跑来祝我好运

84
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,420
That's sweet.
那真的是太好了

85
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:40,570
No,it was more like a "good luck."
不，她的意思是“祝你好运”

86
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,200
So,what did this woman look like?
那个女人长什么样子？

87
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:46,700
She was, like, 30, dark hair, attractive.
她大概三十岁 深色头发，很漂亮

88
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:51,350
Any chance you were looking into a bright, shiny thing called a mirror?
你该不会是刚好 看到一种叫做镜子的东西吧？

89
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:54,170
Was it someone you dated in college?
她会是你大学时的女朋友吗？

90
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:56,680
No, I only dated two girls in college...
不，在大学时 我只交过两个女朋友…

91
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:00,290
both blond, both not attractive.
她们都是金发，也不漂亮

92
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,850
Let me check this out.
让我看看

93
00:06:03,060 --> 00:06:05,720
-What are you doing? -Well,let's see.
-你在做什么？ -来瞧瞧吧

94
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,760
Okay, is that her?
好吧，是她吗？

95
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,360
Oh, my God, yes!
我的天啊，没错

96
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:14,260
-Who is she? -Julie Graff, my camp girlfriend.
-她是谁？ -茱丽葛拉菲，我的夏令营女朋友

97
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:17,100
Did you break up with her?
你跟她分手了？

98
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:19,900
No, we're still together.
不，我们还在一起

99
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:27,410
We went out for two summers and then I broke up with her.
我们交往了两个暑假 后来我跟她分手了

100
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:29,780
-Why? -She came back the third summer...
-为什么？ -第三年的暑假…

101
00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:33,610
and she'd gotten really fa..
她变得有一点…

102
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:39,120
-Fat? -I did not say fat.
-胖？ -我没有那么说

103
00:06:39,390 --> 00:06:41,990
I said fa..
我是说…

104
00:06:43,130 --> 00:06:46,070
You broke up with a girl because she was fat?
你只因为女生胖 就跟她分手？

105
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:48,060
Yeah. Yeah.
对

106
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:52,570
But it was a really long time ago. Does she still feel bad?
但那真的是很久以前的事了 她还在难过吗？

107
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:54,110
Apparently she does.
看起来是的

108
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:57,240
You know what they say: "Elephants never forget."
有句俗话说： “大象永远都不会忘记”

109
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,920
Seriously, good luck marrying me.
说真的，祝你好运

110
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:09,520
Hey, what's going on?
嘿，发生了什么事？

111
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,730
She's Monica's maid of honor.
她是摩妮卡的伴娘

112
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:16,300
Hope it goes better than the last time you did it for that girl downstairs.
希望这次会比上次 你帮楼下那个女孩当伴娘顺利

113
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:21,160
You have been maid of honor before?
你以前当过伴娘？

114
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:25,140
You see? This is exactly why you shouldn't lie.
你看吧？ 那就是人不能说谎的原因

115
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:28,030
That's it. I am maid of honor.
够了，我是伴娘

116
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,370
-No,I am. -How come you are?
-不，我才是 -为什么？

117
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:33,270
Because I cared enough to lie.
因为我在乎到不惜说谎

118
00:07:33,650 --> 00:07:36,310
Hey,I could help you decide who should do it.
我可以帮你们决定 该由谁来当伴娘

119
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,980
We could have an audition.
我们应该办甄试会

120
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:41,310
See how you'd handle maid-of-honor-type situations.
看看你们当伴娘时 会怎么处理突发状况

121
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,750
-What do you mean? -When I want a job...
-你是什么意思 -当我需要一份工作时…

122
00:07:43,990 --> 00:07:47,020
I audition and if I'm the best of the people they see...
我会去试镜 如果他们觉得我是最棒的…

123
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,180
I get the part.
我就可以演出

124
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,330
So, okay, so after this audition, who decides who gets it?
好了，甄试完毕后 谁来决定伴娘人选？

125
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:53,760
Oh,me and Ross can be the judges.
我跟罗斯可以当评审

126
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:56,870
-It's better than us deciding. -Oh, this is crazy.
-这要比让我们自己来决定好 -这太疯狂了

127
00:07:57,140 --> 00:08:00,700
-Can't we just flip a coin? -No, coins hate me.
-我们不能丢铜板决定吗？ -不，铜板恨我

128
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:05,510
Okay, fine. You know what? We will let Ross and Joey decide.
好吧，你知道吗？ 我们让罗斯跟乔伊来决定

129
00:08:06,410 --> 00:08:07,680
Hi!
嗨

130
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,150
Ross, sweetie.
罗斯，甜心

131
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:15,290
Hey there, handsome thing.
你好，大帅哥

132
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:23,230
Wow, this cologne really is every bit as good as Giorgio.
这种古龙水跟亚曼尼的一样棒

133
00:08:29,570 --> 00:08:30,730
Hey.
嘿

134
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:34,030
Just brought back your videos.
我把录影带拿来还你

135
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:38,180
Hey, Ross. Look, I think we need to talk about before.
罗斯，听着 我想我们需要谈谈之前的事

136
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:40,350
No. No, we don't.
不，千万别提那件事

137
00:08:40,780 --> 00:08:41,770
Yes, we do.
不，我们非谈不可

138
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:45,550
Now, look. That was the best nap I ever had.
好了，听我说 那是我睡得最香甜的一觉

139
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,050
I don't know what you're talking about.
我不知道你在说什么

140
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,260
Come on, admit it.
少来了，承认吧

141
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:57,560
That was the best nap you ever had.
那是你睡过最香甜的一觉

142
00:08:58,730 --> 00:09:00,360
I've had better.
我有过更棒的经验

143
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,900
Okay. When?
好吧，什么时候？

144
00:09:05,610 --> 00:09:08,580
All right! All right! It was the best nap ever!
好吧，好吧 那是我睡过最香甜的一觉

145
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:10,280
I said it, okay?
我承认，好吗？

146
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,450
But it's over, Joey!
但那都已经过去了，乔伊

147
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,040
I want to do it again.
我想再来一次

148
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:22,090
We can't do it again.
我们不能再来一次

149
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:24,760
-Why not? -Because it's weird!
-为什么？ -因为那太奇怪了

150
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:27,660
Fine.
好吧

151
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,050
You want a drink?
你想喝点东西吗？

152
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:33,790
-Sure. What do you got? -Warm milk and Excedrin PM.
-好啊，你有什么？ -温牛奶跟抗组胺药

153
00:09:41,910 --> 00:09:43,400
Chandler.
钱德

154
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,580
I just figured out who you are.
我刚刚才知道你是谁

155
00:09:46,810 --> 00:09:49,040
Can you figure out what I'm doing?
你知道我在做什么吗？

156
00:09:50,450 --> 00:09:53,080
-You're Louis Posen. -Who?
-你是路易斯波森 -谁？

157
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:56,550
He was my best friend in fifth grade.
他是我五年级时最好的朋友

158
00:09:56,760 --> 00:10:00,120
One day,I asked him to be my boyfriend and he said no.
有一天我要他当我男朋友 他拒绝了

159
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:01,550
Do you know why?
你知道为什么吗？

160
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:06,030
Because you kept talking to him while he was trying to go to the bathroom?
因为他上厕所时 你一直在跟他说话？

161
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:09,770
No,but because he thought I was too fa..
不，因为他觉得我太…

162
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:15,240
Every time I think about it, I feel as bad as I did then.
每次想到这件事 我还是会觉得很难过

163
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:18,040
I really think you should apologize to Julie.
我真的觉得你该跟茱丽道歉

164
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:21,370
Honey, are you kidding? That was like 16 years ago.
甜心，你在开玩笑吗？ 那是十六年前的事

165
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:25,380
It would make me feel better if Louis apologized to me.
如果路易斯能跟我道歉 我会觉得好过一点

166
00:10:25,590 --> 00:10:29,150
I'll do it. But I warn you, this may make me a better person.
我会跟她道歉，但我警告你 这会让我变成更棒的男人

167
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:32,090
And that is not the man you fell in love with.
而那不是你爱上的那个男人

168
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:38,160
Okay, we'll give you hypothetical maid-of-honor situations.
好吧，我们会假设突发状况 来考验你们当伴娘的资格

169
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,800
You'll be scored on a scale of one to ten.
计分范围从一分到十分

170
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,440
-One being the highest. -Ten is the highest.
-一分是最高分 -十分才是最高分

171
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,940
-Why is 10 the highest? -Because it's the highest.
-为什么十分是最高分？ -因为它是最大的数字

172
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:52,140
Okay, Rachel, you're up first.
好了，瑞秋，你先来

173
00:10:52,350 --> 00:10:55,080
Situation number one: You're with Monica.
一号突发状况 你跟摩妮卡在一起

174
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:59,480
The wedding is about to start when Monica gets cold feet. Go!
婚礼就要开始了 摩妮卡想临阵脱逃，开始

175
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,950
I don't want to marry Chandler.
我不想嫁给钱德

176
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:04,380
-I've got cold feet. -It's gonna be okay.
-我想临阵脱逃 -没事的

177
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:07,030
One man the rest of my life? I don't know.
跟一个男人共度一生？ 我不知道

178
00:11:07,230 --> 00:11:09,750
This means I'll never get to sleep with Joey.
这表示我永远 都不能跟乔伊上床了

179
00:11:12,230 --> 00:11:14,260
Look, Monica...
听我说，摩妮卡…

180
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:16,590
getting cold feet is very common.
临阵脱逃是常见的事

181
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:19,240
It's just because of all the anticipation.
那是因为你期待过高

182
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:23,600
And you just have to remember that you love Chandler.
你只要记住你爱钱德

183
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,370
And also,I ran out on a wedding.
我也逃婚过

184
00:11:26,610 --> 00:11:29,050
You don't get to keep the gifts.
逃婚的人得退还礼物

185
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:32,180
Drawing on your own experience.
你引述亲身经验

186
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:33,610
Very good.
非常好

187
00:11:33,850 --> 00:11:36,190
Yes, very nice, Rachel.
没错，很好，瑞秋

188
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:37,620
Thank you, judges.
谢谢评审

189
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,880
-Kiss ass. -Oh.
-马屁精 -喔

190
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:44,060
-Okay, Phoebe. -Yes, Your Honor.
-好了，菲比 -是的，大人

191
00:11:45,070 --> 00:11:46,860
We're now in the ceremony.
婚礼举行到一半

192
00:11:47,070 --> 00:11:49,090
Monica is about to say, "I do"...
摩妮卡正要说我愿意的时候…

193
00:11:49,370 --> 00:11:51,700
when her drunk uncle starts yelling.
可是她的叔叔喝得烂醉 开始乱吼乱叫

194
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:53,270
What do you do? Go!
你会怎么做？开始

195
00:11:53,540 --> 00:11:56,100
When Monica was a little girl...
摩妮卡还小的时候…

196
00:11:56,310 --> 00:11:58,240
I remember that..
我记得…

197
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,550
Ow!
好痛！

198
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:04,220
-Very good! -Oh.
-非常好 -喔

199
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:06,820
Yes,excellent. Perfect score.
好极了，我给你满分

200
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:10,460
She just made a scene in the middle of the ceremony!
她破坏了正在进行中的婚礼

201
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,460
Hey, you want a little taste of Phoebe?
嘿，你想尝尝菲比的厉害吗？

202
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:18,930
It is time for you to give your maid-of-honor speech.
现在你们得以伴娘的身份 说出对新人的贺词

203
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:20,620
We haven't even prepared..
我们还没有准备…

204
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:23,170
-Go! -Okay, okay, okay.
-开始 -好吧

205
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:26,840
Webster's Dictionary defines marriage as..
韦伯斯特大字典 对婚姻的定义是…

206
00:12:27,070 --> 00:12:31,530
Okay, no! Forget that! That sucks! Okay,never mind. Forget it.
好了，不，忘了它，那段贺词太烂了 别在意，忘了它吧

207
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:36,740
I met.. I met Monica when we were just a couple of 6-year-olds...
我遇见…我认识摩妮卡时 我们只是六岁大的小女孩…

208
00:12:36,950 --> 00:12:41,850
and became friends with Chandler when he was 25...
我们在钱德二十五岁时 成了朋友…

209
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,460
although he seemed like a 6-year-old.
虽然他看起来 很像六岁大的孩子

210
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:46,680
Oh.
喔

211
00:12:47,430 --> 00:12:49,660
Thank you. Thank you very much.
谢谢，感激不尽

212
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,300
I've known them separately and together.
我看过他们单身 跟交往时的样子

213
00:12:54,570 --> 00:12:59,670
To know them as a couple is to know that you are in the presence of love.
我知道他们交往时 深爱着彼此

214
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:03,210
So I would like to raise my glass...
现在我想举杯…

215
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:05,110
to Monica and Chandler...
敬摩妮卡跟钱德…

216
00:13:05,310 --> 00:13:09,810
and the beautiful adventure they are about to embark upon together.
还有他们要携手共度的 美好冒险历程

217
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:13,680
I can think of no two people better prepared for the journey.
我认为他们做好了 万全的准备要展开这段旅程

218
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:16,120
Wow.
哇

219
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:19,690
-Great speech. -Yeah, it really was.
-说的好 -没错，真的很棒

220
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:20,920
Oh,thanks.
谢谢

221
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:26,030
Okay, Phoebe, I guess you're next. Although I really don't see the point.
好了，菲比，下一个是你 虽然我觉得那么做是多余的

222
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,630
Okay.
好吧

223
00:13:32,810 --> 00:13:36,270
I can't believe that Monica and Chandler are getting married.
我不敢相信摩妮卡 跟钱德要结婚了

224
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:39,070
I remember talking about this day with Rachel...
我还记得 我跟瑞秋谈过这一天…

225
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:42,110
while we were showering together, naked.
那时我们一起冲澡 全身一丝不挂

226
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,710
And she's back in the game!
她大逆转了

227
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,560
Julie. Hi.
茱丽，嗨

228
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:05,030
Chandler Bing. I guess you remember me.
我是钱德宾 我猜你还记得我

229
00:14:05,340 --> 00:14:07,330
Hello, Skidmark.
你好，备胎

230
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,580
It's a nickname. I'll explain later.
那是我的绰号，待会再跟你解释

231
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,640
It's pretty clear.
我看得出来原因

232
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:20,950
I owe you a long,overdue apology.
我很早以前就该跟你道歉

233
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:24,610
I shouldn't have broken up with you because of your weight.
我不该只因为你很胖 就跟你分手

234
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:27,360
That's why you broke up with me?
那是你跟我分手的原因？

235
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,800
You didn't know that?
你不知道啊？

236
00:14:34,770 --> 00:14:37,100
Well, I guess my work here is done.
看来我的任务已经达成

237
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:46,680
First of all, I would like to say you both performed very well, okay?
但首先我要说 你们两个都表现的很好，好吗？

239
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:48,470
You should be proud.
你们应该觉得骄傲

240
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:53,480
And I'd also like to say, in this competition, there are no losers.
我还想说在这场比赛里 没有人是输家

241
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,020
Well, except Rachel. Damn it!
瑞秋除外，该死

242
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,220
Really? I won.
真的吗？我赢了

243
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:02,400
-What? -I'm sorry, Rach, it was really close.
-什么？ -对不起，瑞秋，分数真的很接近

244
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:06,330
-Well, then I demand a recount! -Actually, it wasn't that close.
-那么我要求重新计分 -事实上也没有那么接近

245
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:09,630
You know what? Your thing was so stupid anyway.
你知道吗？ 反正你们的方法太愚蠢了

246
00:15:09,870 --> 00:15:12,100
We're gonna flip a coin, all right?
我们来丢铜板决定，好吗？

247
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:13,900
Heads.
正面

248
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:18,470
What? The coins have finally forgiven me!
什么？铜板终于原谅我了

249
00:15:19,810 --> 00:15:23,310
Know what? I hope Monica forgives you after you throw her...
你知道吗？我希望摩妮卡 会原谅你，因为你会用…

250
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:28,610
vegetarian-voodoo-goddess-circle-y shower.
用怪力乱神的素食主义方式 对着她洒花片

251
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:33,630
Rach, it's gonna be okay. You guys are the best!
瑞秋，没关系的 你们帅呆了

252
00:15:35,930 --> 00:15:39,660
Boy, I tell you. That judging stuff took a lot out of me.
天啊，我得告诉你 当评审真的把我累坏了

253
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,030
-Yeah? -Yeah.
-是吗？ -没错

254
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:45,500
Thinking about maybe going upstairs and taking a little nap on my couch.
我想或许我该上楼去 在我的沙发上好好睡一觉

255
00:15:48,710 --> 00:15:51,140
Why would I care about that?
那关我什么事？

256
00:15:52,450 --> 00:15:55,510
No reason. I'm just saying that...
不为什么，我只是说…

257
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,010
that's where I'll be.
我会在那里

258
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:21,670
As bad as that went, I actually enjoyed myself.
虽然结局不如预期中理想 事实上我很满意自己的表现

259
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:26,210
I think that I'm going to apologize for all the stupid things that I do.
我想我要为我做过的 所有蠢事道歉

260
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:28,970
Why don't you just stop doing stupid things?
你为什么不改掉 做蠢事的习惯？

261
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:33,310
-Then you wouldn't have to apologize. -I'd love it if I could do both.
-那样子你就不必道歉了 -我希望可以两个一起做

262
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:39,280
All right, I have to ask.
好吧，我得问你

263
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,780
What?
什么？

264
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:44,390
Will you break up with me if I get fat?
如果我变胖了 你会跟我分手吗？

265
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:45,760
What?
什么？

266
00:16:45,970 --> 00:16:49,270
You broke up with Julie. How much weight did she gain?
你跟茱丽分手 她变得有多胖呢？

267
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:51,800
A hundred and forty-five pounds.
她胖了一百四十五磅

268
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,500
In one year?
在一年之内？

269
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,970
My God, what did she eat? Her family?
天啊，她吃了什么？ 她的家人吗？

270
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,110
That's not the point.
那不是重点

271
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:05,270
I know it was a stupid reason to break up with someone, but I was 15.
我知道那样子跟别人分手太蠢了 但当时我才十五岁

272
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:09,720
Yeah, well, that's not the only time this was an issue.
对，不只十五岁的男孩 觉得肥胖是个问题

273
00:17:11,230 --> 00:17:14,220
You remember when you spent Thanksgiving with us?
你还记得 你跟我们一起过感恩节的事吗？

274
00:17:14,430 --> 00:17:15,520
You called me fat.
你骂我胖

275
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,920
Wait a minute.
等一下

276
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:19,760
-That was totally different. -How?
-那完全是另一回事 -怎么说？

277
00:17:19,970 --> 00:17:23,770
You were not supposed to hear that. I said that behind your back.
你不该听到那句话 我是在你背后偷偷说的

278
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:28,540
What if I have babies, okay? I'm gonna look different.
如果我怀孕了呢？ 我会变得跟现在不一样

279
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:31,300
I'm okay with that, but I'm not sure you are.
我可以接受那样的事 但我不相信你能做到

280
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:35,470
You have to realize I don't think of you as a thin, beautiful woman.
你得了解我不认为 你是个苗条的大美女

281
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:43,010
This is one of the things that I can apologize for later.
我待会儿就会为这种事情道歉

282
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:47,120
What I mean is,you're Monica.
我是说你是摩妮卡

283
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:50,390
Okay? And I am in love with Monica.
我吗？我爱上的人是摩妮卡

284
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,260
Keep going.
继续说

285
00:17:52,470 --> 00:17:56,490
So you can balloon up or you can shrink down...
不论你变胖或是变瘦…

286
00:17:56,770 --> 00:17:58,700
and I will still love you.
我还是会爱你

287
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:03,540
Even if I were to shrink down to 2 inches tall?
即使我缩小到只有两寸高？

288
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:06,570
I'd carry you around in my pocket.
我会把你放在我的口袋里

289
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,140
I love you.
我爱你

290
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:15,410
Skidmark still got a way with the ladies.
备胎还是对女人很有一套

291
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:19,480
Hi,Phoebe.
嗨，菲比

292
00:18:19,690 --> 00:18:21,090
-Hi. -Hi.
-嗨 -嗨

293
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:22,990
I just want to apologize.
我来跟你道歉

294
00:18:23,230 --> 00:18:25,600
I'm really sorry I was a baby.
我真的很抱歉我太孩子气了

295
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:29,360
That's ridiculous. Rachel, we were all babies once.
那太可笑了 瑞秋，我们都曾经是小孩子

296
00:18:32,010 --> 00:18:34,100
Oh, you mean today. Yeah.
你是说今天的事，没错

297
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:38,570
Yeah, and you know, you deserve to win.
对，你知道吗？ 你应该赢的

298
00:18:38,950 --> 00:18:40,680
And I was thinking about it.
我一直在想这件事

299
00:18:40,910 --> 00:18:44,040
If you're Monica's maid of honor, I get to be yours.
如果你是摩妮卡的伴娘 那我就是你的伴娘

300
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:46,340
-Oh,yeah. -Yeah.
-没错 -对

301
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:52,020
When Monica and Chandler got engaged, I put some stuff together.
摩妮卡跟钱德订婚时 我收集了一些东西

302
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:55,130
-Just in case. -Oh, that's so sweet. Thanks.
-以防万一 -那真的是太好了，谢谢

303
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,630
Here is a book of poetry that I know Monica loves.
我知道摩妮卡 很喜欢这本诗集

304
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:01,060
Oh, God, this is funny. Look.
天啊，这真有趣，你看

305
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:05,070
Here's a picture from one Halloween when she dressed up as a bride.
这是有一年万圣节 她打扮成新娘的照片

306
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:06,900
She made me carry her train...
她要我帮她拉婚纱

307
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:10,240
which was weird because I was Wonder Woman.
那真的很奇怪 因为我扮的是神力女超人

308
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:14,640
Oh, and here's a little purse that I found.
喔，这是我发现的小包包

309
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,720
I just thought they could hold the rings in there.
我想应该可以把婚戒放在这里

310
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:20,580
-Oh. -Something. And...
-喔 -还有…

311
00:19:20,790 --> 00:19:25,350
vintage handkerchiefs, you know, because people cry at weddings.
上好的手帕 因为很多人会在婚礼哭

312
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:27,990
I'm just gonna grab a couple of these.
我得拿几条走

313
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:31,490
This stuff is great.
这真的是棒极了

314
00:19:31,730 --> 00:19:34,060
I forgot this was in here.
我都忘了我把它放在这里

315
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:40,130
This was the garter that I was saving for my wedding.
这是我留下来 要在自己婚礼上用的吊袜带

316
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:44,070
And I wanted it to be Monica's "something borrowed."
我希望它能成为 被摩妮卡“借走的东西”

317
00:19:44,780 --> 00:19:46,080
And it's blue.
它是蓝色的

318
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:55,510
Rach, I think that you should be Monica's maid of honor.
瑞秋，我认为你应该 当摩妮卡的伴娘

319
00:19:57,590 --> 00:19:59,080
You do?
真的吗？

320
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:03,260
-Why? -Because I think it means more to you.
-为什么？ -因为我想这对你来说意义重大

321
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,430
But, Phoebe, honey, you earned it.
但菲比，你赢了

322
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:08,760
It's fine. I mean, this is something...
没关系，我是说…

323
00:20:08,970 --> 00:20:12,630
that you've been thinking about since you were, what, 14?
你从十四岁就想这么做了吧？

324
00:20:12,970 --> 00:20:15,970
No, I was 10. I just developed early.
不，那时我才十岁 我发育的很早

325
00:20:16,780 --> 00:20:18,770
Man alive!
我的天啊

326
00:20:21,650 --> 00:20:23,480
-Hey, what's going on? -Hey!
-嘿，怎么了？ -嘿

327
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:26,780
We just decided Rachel is going to be your maid of honor.
我们刚决定由瑞秋来当你的伴娘

328
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:29,520
Oh, that's great!
那真的是太棒了

329
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:33,120
Oh, wow. Okay, we really have to start planning.
哇，太棒了 我们得开始计划

330
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,420
I have really specific ideas.
我有很多特别的好点子

331
00:20:35,660 --> 00:20:37,690
We should meet four times a week.
我们应该一星期开四次会

332
